main event: Two radar-detected objects were observed near Los Angeles International Airport, initially detected as two, then one, traveling at approximately 3000 mph.
interesting points: The objects were rectangular and were first detected at 30,000 feet., They moved towards the station from about 10 miles away., At one point, they stopped and then accelerated to a speed of 220 knots., The sighting concluded that it could possibly be a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomena., The radar at the station experienced high voltage loss, affecting detection capabilities.
witness description: Civilian air operation specialist, reliable observer at the control tower
